oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Tabard II Inn
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the exterior of the Tabard II Inn. Several unidentified people are gathered on the front porch. The first Tabard Inn was destroyed by fire in the early 1880s, and the Tabard II Inn was built to replace it. The second Tabard Inn burned in 1899.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Taverns (Inns); People
